:"cm-dif-articles-motivation","key":"SIIovGvPGw"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Traditionally journal publications have been stand alone research articles, often with a format of abstract, introduction, methods, results and discussion sections.","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"key":"kmCjfYgijo"}],"key":"FrhiOgR8Kd"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This format was often quite limiting and meant things like datasets, software (scripts, code, apps, tools) and methods were often squeezed into research articles with little detail due to word limits, hidden in supplementary material or not included at all.","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"NuOiZ1QZeH"}],"key":"egly2zmA8O"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Researchers therefore increasingly deposit these research objects in repositories to make them usable and discoverable by others.\nDepositing them with rich metadata and linking to a research articles is best practice and you can find out more about how to do that in our ","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"key":"W39j9auhy3"},{"type":"link","url":"https://book.the-turing-way.org/communication/citable.html","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Making Research Objects Citable chapter","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"key":"s4iDKoDqWF"}],"urlSource":"https://book.the-turing-way.org/communication/citable.html","key":"N3alTzgMEL"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"key":"quwd3a9may"}],"key":"Xxdxt6fHR4"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":48,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, recently there has been the development of new article types, which allows all deposited research outputs produced during the research lifecycle to be published in their own right and further linked to the final interpretations and conclusions of a research project.\nThe linking of these articles is one way to fully publish a reproducible research project.","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"key":"VgujavdiEG"}],"key":"xfqrVWlbht"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Having separate article types for these outputs allows the people involved, such as research software engineers and data stewards, to receive sufficient credit, attribution and visibility for their work and contributions, particularly as publications are still the main currency by which researchers are evaluated.","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"wOJ2S3nSn1"}],"key":"qwAYsBYQTb"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":1},"end":{"line":52,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Theses articles are also important for the sustainability, reproducibility and openness of these research outputs as writing detailed publications means greater care and attention is directed at describing and explaining these outputs and in turn makes these outputs more FAIR (findable, accessible, interoperable and reusable).","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":1},"end":{"line":52,"column":1}},"key":"fXOV5kQYW6"}],"key":"mkS6sTz81n"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note: in this chapter and subchapter we are using the word ‘article’ and ‘paper’ interchangeably.","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"key":"b5dvmuH7qR"}],"key":"uIgNBuvZQj"}],"key":"cp2R9VLMJF"}],"key":"mn7jVoXWyO"},"references":{"cite":{"order":["https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3332807"],"data":{"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3332807":{"label":"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3332807","enumerator":"1","doi":"10.5281/ZENODO.3332807","html":"The Turing Way Community, & Scriberia. (2024). <i>Illustrations from The Turing Way: Shared under CC-BY 4.0 for reuse</i>. Zenodo. <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.3332807\">10.5281/ZENODO.3332807</a>","url":"https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.3332807"}}}}}